video.title: Crazy Land
video.synopsis: Each episode of this series centers on Americans who live a step or two out of the ordinary, from real-life superheroes to sumo wrestlers.

episodes.synopsis: Meet the homespun vigilantes who don masks, capes and tights to fight crime on their cities' streets, sometimes at risk to their own lives.
episodes.title: Real Life Super Heroes

episodes.synopsis: Too much isn't enough for the men and women at Texas's Metroflex gym, where extreme bodybuilders build monster muscle beyond the norm.
episodes.title: Extreme Body Builders

episodes.synopsis: This episode visits the Dallas County Jail, home to 6,500 inmates, for a look at the modern American justice system.
episodes.title: Jail

episodes.synopsis: With the prevalence of piercings and tattoos, some folks have chosen to take body modification a bit farther, from split tongues to horn implants.
episodes.title: Body Modification

episodes.synopsis: American sumo wrestlers discuss what draws them to the ancient Japanese martial arts form and reveal how the sport differs in the United States.
episodes.title: Sumo

episodes.synopsis: Meet the members of the Alliance, who regularly dress as wizards, elves and other fantastic creatures to do battle in live-action role play (LARP).
episodes.title: LARPing

episodes.synopsis: This episode spotlights luchadores, Mexican-American wrestlers who risk injury for love of the sport and the attention of a good crowd.
episodes.title: Mexican Wrestling (Luche Libre)

episodes.synopsis: The members of the Michigan Militia, a private civilian army, grab their automatic weapons and prepare for an invasion from China.
episodes.title: Militias
